Paper: hep-th/9808067

Date: 1998-08-12

Title: Finite VEVs from a Large Distance Vacuum Wave Functional

Authors: A. Jaramillo (U. Valencia, Spain), P. Mansfield (U. Durham, UK)

Comments: 39 pages, 16 figures, LaTeX2e using package graphicx

Journal-ref: Int.J.Mod.Phys. A15 (2000) 581-600

We show how to compute vacuum expectation values from derivative expansionsof the vacuum wave functional. Such expansions appear to be valid only forslowly varying fields, but by exploiting analyticity in a complex scaleparameter we can reconstruct the contribution from rapidly varying fields.